name: Blues From A Spaceship In C

content.text:
This is by a band called the KGB.  They're really cool and
they will defintely get super big one day.
anyway,  these guys are definetly hot 3 chord punk so it's
a little bit harder to figure out the chords.  but this is
one of their more simpler songs.  at the end of "in case of
a bad trip", theres a really cool acoustic song which is "Blues From A Spaceship in C" and the whole thing is in Chords.  It's not hard:


    [ch]C[/ch]    [ch]G[/ch]    [ch]Am[/ch]   [ch]C[/ch]    [ch]F[/ch]    [ch]C[/ch]    [ch]F[/ch]    [ch]G[/ch]
E --0----3----0----0----1----0----1----3
B --1----3----1----1----1----1----1----3
G --0----0----2----0----2----0----2----0
D --2----0----2----2----3----2----3----0
A --3----2----0----3----0----3----0----2
E --0----3----0----0---------0---------3

Yeah so just repeat throughout the song and the lyrics are:

Blues from a spaceship in C
and would you believe that the world isn't such a bad place
and the clouds that will all be erased
will all be replaced
as the world rotates slowly in space
and i think i've forgotten your name
it's more of the same
with the rhyme that escaped from my brain
It's my song, it's my love, it's my curse
I'm a victim of verse
Since the day that I fell through the Earth
It's the hope and the truth that collide
and I'm burning inside
with a feeling i could not describe
if i try, oh if i try

Rosie come out of your trance
There's not second chance
With the moment that slipped through your hands
It's a  moment beyond your command


k thats the end
enjoy......
-kgbaren 11/17/01

                            "Sail On Sailor"
     (J. Rieley / R. Kennedy / B. Wilson / T. Almer / V. D. Parks)

This is the version as performed by one of the song's writer's, Ray Kennedy (RIP), 

in the (super) group KGB and other live performances. He claimed these were the 

original lyrics.

Having had to get this version from the KGB recording, I'm not 100% sure about some 

of the words. The Beachboys version is very different and obviously had a set of 

sanitised lyrics written for radio consumption. So, there may be a mondegreen or 2 

in there. Feel free to fix em.

			     KGB – Kaizers Orchestra
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Tabbed by: Robert Ippolito


Tuning: Standard (EADGBe)


Right, quite often it is hard to tab Kaizers Orchestra because the guitars are usually
minimalistic, therefore I find it a little bit silly to listen through a song a million
writing down every little twang and odd harmonic that might come up. Try different 
patterns, variation in how hard you hit the strings, adding suspended
etc. to add variation to the places where the chords don’t change much.
